{"title":"Spotted: Prototype SRAM Level Brake Levers give Lars Forster’s Scott Spark better hose angle?","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/17/spotted-prototype-sram-level-brake-levers-give-lars-forsters-scott-spark-better-hose-angle/","date":1631909768000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--800x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up-.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-272030\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Snowshoe World Cup week is solidly under way, and the pro race bike checks are starting to trickle in. While the DH double header may be the star attraction of the program, there is still plenty to be seen on the XC side as well. While taking a look at Lars Forster’s Scott Spark, Jordan noticed a peculiar setup at the brake levers…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-.jpg\" alt=\"Prototype SRAM Level Brake Levers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151057/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>At the end of what appears to be a SRAM Level Ultimate lever, the hose on Lars’ brakes angles up instead of straight out like the current Level brakes. It’s quite possible there have been other changes to the lever (the Ultimate doesn’t include a tool-free reach adjust aluminum brake lever for instance, but for the post part the change looks to be an attempt to tidy up the front end of the bike. <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up-.jpg\" alt=\"Prototype SRAM Level Brake Levers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151059/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-bars-set-up--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The angled hoses allow them to hug closer to the bar, keeping a portion of the cable nest behind the number plate. It seems like this would be more beneficial on bars with bigger backsweep numbers which could be welcomed outside the racing world as well.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors-.jpg\" alt=\"Prototype SRAM Level Brake Levers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151111/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-fork-with-new-rotors--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors.jpg\" alt=\"Prototype SRAM Level Brake Levers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151116/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-new-sram-rotors-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>From the outside, the Level brake calipers appear to be unchanged, and Lars is running the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/01/sram-hs2-mtb-brake-rotor-gets-new-brake-track-and-thermal-dissipating-paint/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">new HS2 brake rotors</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset-.jpg\" alt=\"Custom Scott TwinLoc lever\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151055/Scott-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-brakeset--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>It’s hard to tell what’s going on at the TwinLoc lever, but this is certainly <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/09/2022-scott-spark-gets-bold-new-redesign-as-a-slack-fast-fully-integrated-120mm-xc-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">not the same triple TwinLock lever</a> you’ll find on the new Scott Spark. Or at least, not without some modification. Complicating things is that Lars’ training bike and race bike have different setups. The training bike shown above uses a mechanical dropper post meaning that lever setup above&nbsp;<em>does </em>function as the TwinLoc 3, but with a different lever setup. His race bike uses an AXS wireless dropper, so where’s the remote?</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664.jpg\" alt=\"Lars Forster\" width=\"843\" height=\"618\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664.jpg 843w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664-297x218.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664-800x586.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664-120x88.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151106/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-clean-rear-view--e1631907658664-768x563.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px\"></a></p><p>If you look closely, that appears to be located on the right side of the bar using a SRAM Blip set up. When we’ve seen this before, it’s required the use of a SRAM Blip Box tucked somewhere in the build. Jordan is getting a better shot of the lever set up soon so we can get a closer look.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg.jpg\" alt=\"Pro-only blackbox power meter crank\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151101/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-Blackbox-Quarg-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side-.jpg\" alt=\"Pro only black box power meter crank\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151118/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-non-drive-side--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><br>We’ve seen a lot of pro-only Black Box Powermeter cranks and Lars’ bike is no different. The 175mm SRam XX1 Eagle Dub SL Black Box power meter has a massive narrow-wide ring and powers a SRAM XX1 Eagle AXS drivetrain.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires-.jpg\" alt=\"maxxis test pilot tires\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires-.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires--297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires--800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires--120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151124/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-test-pilot-tires--768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin.jpg\" alt=\"maxxis test pilot tires\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/17151113/Scott-SRAM-Spark-Lars-Forester-Bike-maxxis-tire-aspin-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Maxxis’ Test Pilot hot patch indicates that these are not your off-the-shelf tires.<